Day 9:
Step 0: Log in to the Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com/).


_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Creating a Snapshot of the VM:
Step 1: Go to the already existing Virtual Machine.
Step 2: In the VM, go to settings and click on disks.
Step 3: Create a new disk and Click on create to CREATE a new snapshot.
Step 4: Enter the following details:
      a. SS Name
      b. Snapshot Type - Full
Step 5: Click on SAVE to save your SS.
Step 6: Create a disk from the Snapshot.


_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


2. Creating Virtual Machine from VHD:
Step 1: Create a Virtual Machine from the Disks.
Step 2: Select create to create a Virtual Machine.
Step 3: Chose the disks created from the snapshot in the DISKS.
Step 4: Go to REVIEW+CREATE and click on CREATE button to create VM.
Step 5: Once deployment is complete, go to RESOURCE to view your VM.

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
